body:
Oh, this is #4913. It should be fixed if you replace

``` rust
#[deriving(...)]
struct Foo { ... }

bar();
baz();
```

with

``` rust
#[deriving(...)]
struct Foo { ... }

fn main() {
   bar();
   baz();
}
```

(that is, give an explicit `main`, which stops rustdoc wrapping the entire example in its own `main`, which hits that issue).
